  "bio": [
    "Cyrus Madon is the executive vice chair of Brookfield Asset Management, a Toronto-based spinoff of Brookfield Corp. which manages $1 trillion in assets.",
    "Madon joined Brookfield in 1998 and was previously the CEO of its private equity business. He remains its executive chair of private equity.",
    "He began his career working in corporate finance at PricewaterhouseCoopers and initially joined Brookfield as CFO of its real estate brokerage business.",
    "Madon also serves on the board of the C.D. Howe Institute, an influential Canadian think tank."
